                    <format attr='background-color' value='#1c2541' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone fixed-size='280' h='42442' id='19' is-fixed='true' name='Heart Disease by Gender' w='27030' x='60061' y='12907'>
                  <layout-cache minheight='223' type-h='scalable' type-w='fixed' />
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#3a506b' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='3' />
                    <_.fcp.DashboardRoundedCorners.true...format attr='corner-radius' value='15' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                    <format attr='background-color' value='#1c2541' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone fixed-size='804' forceUpdate='true' h='60000' id='22' type-v2='text' w='10242' x='89030' y='38372'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>1. Heart disease prevalence increases significantly after age 50.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>2. Males show a higher incidence of heart disease compared to females.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>3. Patients with </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#ffffff'>asymptomatic chest pain </run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>have higher heart disease risk</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>4. Lower maximum heart rate is strongly associated with heart disease.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>5. Exercise-induced angina is a major risk indicator.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>6. Patients with more major vessels colored (ca 2 1) show higher disease probability.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#ffffff'>7. Cholesterol alone is not a decisive factor - needs to be combined with other metrics.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
